to accession china's corn prices were estimated to be more than 30 percent above world market prices huang rozelle and chang 2003 china's government explicitly admitted to providing subsidies for corn exports of up to us35 per metric which accounted for almost all of the protection that corn producers in china were receiving during the late 1990s and through 2001 with such high subsidies the nation's exporters were able to sell around 5 million metric tons mmts annually into world markets gale 2003 most of the shipments especially in the 2000 and 2001 were sent to korea and malaysia with such large shipments the exports of other nations in the world especially those from the us that traditionally was korea's main supplier of feed grains were displaced download pdf+ complete modified april 2007 pdf corn_trade_china_july2003_fina pdf 1001.3 kb pdf+ executive summary modified april 2007 pdf corn_trade_china_executive_sum pdf 12.2 kb topics world trade organization china malaysia south korea search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publications of interest trade and investment liberalization til and china's rural economy impacts and policy responses after china's accession to the wto scott rozelle world bank 2002 pdf+ hindering trade or protecting the developing world assessing the impact of the biosafety protocol for the case of china scott rozelle jikun huang delian zhang jun yang nicholas kalaitzandonakes 2006 pdf+ yen the yuan and the asian currency crisis changing fortune between japan and china the ch kwan shorenstein aparc 1998 pdf+ international organizations and democratization testing the effect of gatt wto membership mary comerford cooper shorenstein aparc 2003 pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
